text:
Ave. U. east of East 16th Street. A view of Ave. U. in or about 1906, prior to the real estate boom.

About 1906.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Ave. U, east of East 16th Street, showing at the right Nos. 1616-1620 Ave. U., which were still standing in 1929. In the foreground are the tracks of the Brighton Beach R.R., which became the Brighton Beach (B.M.T.) line; beyond is the Long Island R.R. (elevated bypass), which was discontinued in 1930.

About 1908.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
